Windows download link:
https://git-for-windows.github.io/

Linux commands
==============

For Linux type the following commands from the shell

$ sudo apt-get update
$ sudo apt-get install git

After Installing you can configure your user name and e-mail id.

$ git config --global user.name "First Last"
$ git config --global user.email "myemail@domain.com"


Basic Terminology:Repo, remote and commit

Commands:
1) Create repository
$ git init project
$ cd project
$ tree .git
$ git init --bare barerepo

Cloning a repo:
===============
git clone repo.git

Entire history of the project
=============================
git log --oneline --graph 

Checking Status
===============
git status
git status -sb (summary branch)

#stage files
git add filename

Commit
======
git commit -m message
or git commit -av # this shows the difference and lets u type message interactively

Advance Commits
git add --patch # hunks //part of fileto 
git commit -v

branching
git checkout -b branchName



git commit -av

git diff <file1> <file2> 
The above command will show the patches of the files that are changed in '@@' blocks. These are known as hunks.
